******
[2] Cholera - Nigeria (Yobe state)
Date: Sun 16 Dec 2018
Source: Reliefweb, a Government of Nigeria report [edited]
https://reliefweb.int/report/nigeria/yobe-state-cholera-outbreak-situation-report-no-68-10th-16th-december-2018


Yobe state cholera outbreak situation report no. 68: 10-16 Dec 2018
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Highlights:
- 0 case was reported
- 0 death was reported.

Epidemiological summary
-----------------------
The total number of suspected cholera cases reported in Yobe state is 1813 with 61 associated deaths (CFR 3.36%). In the state, up to 591 cases have been reported in Gulani LGA, 485 cases in Gujba LGA and 489 cases in Damaturu LGA. In Fune LGA, 181 cases were reported and 67 cases were reported in Potiskum LGA.

Out of 148 samples collected and tested using cholera RDTs, 133 (89.9%) were positive and 15 (10.1%) were negative. Again, 13 (57%) out of 23 samples cultured were positive for _Vibrio cholerae_. However, 9 positive samples were taken to national reference laboratory for quality checks and further analysis samples. _V. cholerae_ O1 (Inaba) serotype was isolated in 4 out of the 9 samples.

No new suspected cholera case was reported in Yobe state from 10 to 16 Dec 2018, showing a possible end to the outbreak. The last case reported was on the 3 Dec 2018. No case was reported from Damaturu. Gulani did not report any case more than 2 weeks. No new case was reported from Gujba in 7 weeks as well as no new case from Fune in 8 weeks and Potiskum LGA has not reported any case in 13 weeks.

--
