[3] Cholera - Nigeria (Borno state)
Date: Sun 16 Dec 2018
Source: Reliefweb, a Government of Nigeria report [edited]
https://reliefweb.int/report/nigeria/situation-report-cholera-outbreak-borno-state-no83-wk-50-10th-16th-december-2018


Situation report of cholera outbreak in Borno state no.83: week 50 (10-16 Dec 2018)
------------------------------------------------------------------
Highlights:
- 12 additional suspected cases of cholera were reported in week 50 in Borno state.
- No death was reported.

Epidemiological summary
-----------------------
The total number of suspected cholera cases reported as at 16 Dec 2018 stands at 6367 with 73 associated deaths, (case fatality rate [CFR] 1.15%); 2482 in Jere, 1556 in MMC, 340 in Magumeri, 34 in Kaga, 166 in Konduga, 136 in Chibok, 11 in Shani, 42 in Damboa, 1052 in Ngala, 91 in Askira-Uba, 161 in Kwaya-Kusar, 56 in Bama, 57 in Dikwa, 70 in Guzamala and 121 in KalaBalge local government areas (LGAs). No additional case reported from Magumeri, Ngala, Askira/Uba, Kaga, Chibok, Dikwa, Shani, Damboa, KwayaKusar, Guzamala, Konduga, Bama and Kala/Balge LGAs.

Out of the 196 samples collected and tested in the state using RDTs (rapid diagnostic tests), 161 (82%) were positive while 40 (44%) of 91 samples were culture positive.

